# Walkthrough - Global Market Dashboard

I have successfully built a premium, real-time stock market dashboard.

## Features
-   **Real-time Simulation**: Graphs update every 2 seconds with simulated tick data.
-   **Global Indices**: Tracks KOSPI, KOSDAQ, NASDAQ, and S&P 500.
-   **Responsive Design**: Grid layout adapts from desktop to mobile.
-   **Visuals**: Dark mode with neon accents (Green for Up, Red for Down), glassmorphism cards, and gradients.

## How to Verify
1.  Navigate to the project folder: `c:\Users\needl\Desktop\예제 9`
2.  Open `index.html` in your web browser (Chrome, Edge, etc.).
3.  **Observation Checklist**:
    -   [ ] Verify all 4 cards appear.
    -   [ ] Watch the "LIVE DATA" indicator blink.
    -   [ ] Wait for 2-3 seconds to see the charts move and prices update.
    -   [ ] Note that the chart color changes to Red if the price drops below the opening price, and Green otherwise.

## Tech Stack
-   **HTML5/CSS3**: No frameworks, pure performance.
-   **Chart.js**: For rendering the canvas-based graphs.
-   **JS**: ES6+ logic for data simulation.

> [!NOTE]
> Values are simulated. To show real data, a backend API key would be required.
